<item>
            <title>[SPARK-32738] thread safe endpoints may hang due to fatal error</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-32738</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Processing for `ThreadSafeRpcEndpoint`&#160;is controlled by &apos;numActiveThreads&apos; in `Inbox`. Now if any fatal error happens during `Inbox.process`,&#160;&apos;numActiveThreads&apos; is not reduced. Then other threads can not process messages in that inbox, which causes the endpoint to &quot;hang&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This problem is more serious in previous Spark 2.x versions since&#160;the driver, executor and block manager endpoints are all thread safe endpoints.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
